description:
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a rare opportunity to join our dynamic and supportive Community Rehabilitation Team. We are looking for a Physiotherapy Clinical Team Lead (30h) who will hold both a complex caseload and lead the team clinically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a friendly and well-established team of Physiotherapists who sit within an integrated multidisciplinary Community Rehabilitation and Urgent Response Teams. The team deal with a varied caseload from falls, respiratory and neurological conditions for people who reside in an attractive mix of towns and rural villages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who will sit within the team, hold a clinical caseload and be aware of the successes and challenges which the team face on a daily basis. The post holder needs to be approachable and transparent with their communication continuing to unite the team and support in the maintenance and development of core and specialist skills. Alongside the clinical skills we are looking for someone who would lead the team, providing clear direction and leadership in Physiotherapy. You will have regular support from professional leads to guide you in both the physiotherapy and trust vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We understand that not all aspiring leaders have Band 7 experience and feel we can offer the support for development in this post, making it suitable for the a Band 6 Physiotherapist with the right vision and skill mix to be supported to develop. On a daily basis you will be working with the Occupational Therapy Clinical Team Lead and the Therapy Manager who provides with operational direction for the team. The leadership team within the cluster work closely together and the focus between the teams is to provide excellent patient care by the right person, in the right place and at the right time through communication and integration. There are frequent changes within Community Services and it is essential that you are a good communicator, flexible and forward thinking to enable to delivery of this service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange a visit please call:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heather Wolhuter (Therapy Manager) 07821813925&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
